                <note rend="inline" type="source">811B.142/4: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-02-24">February 24,
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>469. American interests—Far East. Reference Department’s 117, January 15, and
                    previous telegrams in regard to transmission of funds to American internees in
                    Philippine Islands.</p>
                <p>In view of desperate need of funds for purchase food and medicines please urge
                    Swiss Government to press for earliest possible solution this problem. In
                    meantime please obtain from Swiss Government statement as to progress thus far
                    made in the matter.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
